Dementias were ranked fourth among the leading causes of death in people aged 
≥70 years in 2000, rising to second place in 2016. In 2016, it also represented 
the second and third leading causes of disability among older women and men, 
respectively.
CONCLUSION: Population growth and aging have resulted in an increased burden of 
AD and other dementias in Brazil. Preventive and early diagnostic measures are 
essential to mitigate the burden associated with these diseases.

